2584
01:41:31,160 --> 01:41:34,020
large mass and smooth potentials,

2585
01:41:34,020 --> 01:41:36,540
is the limit of classical physics.

2586
01:41:36,940 --> 01:41:41,620
Light mass and abrupt potentials is more quantum mechanical.

2587
01:41:42,580 --> 01:41:43,200
Yeah?

2588
01:41:44,100 --> 01:41:45,940
Just to get a feel for

2589
01:41:45,940 --> 01:41:47,780
what you mean by large and small,

2590
01:41:48,240 --> 01:41:49,200
if you,

2591
01:41:49,200 --> 01:41:52,950
is an electron large enough to

2592
01:41:52,950 --> 01:41:56,700
behave classically as it's flying around?

2593
01:41:59,420 --> 01:42:01,090
It's an interplay between the shape

2594
01:42:01,090 --> 01:42:02,760
of the potential and the mass.

2595
01:42:04,020 --> 01:42:05,560
If you take a very,

2596
01:42:05,560 --> 01:42:10,660
very smooth potential of the kind that you might make,

2597
01:42:10,780 --> 01:42:11,160
let's say,

2598
01:42:11,160 --> 01:42:13,080
with a couple of capacitor plates,

2599
01:42:14,259 --> 01:42:16,680
capacitor plates separated by a meter,

2600
01:42:16,780 --> 01:42:17,100
well,

2601
01:42:17,100 --> 01:42:18,720
we don't have to take a meter or a centimeter,

2602
01:42:20,900 --> 01:42:23,660
with a smooth electric field between them,

2603
01:42:25,139 --> 01:42:28,209
then the electron will move

2604
01:42:28,209 --> 01:42:31,280
through it as a nice coherent,

2605
01:42:31,280 --> 01:42:32,720
almost classical particle.

2606
01:42:34,020 --> 01:42:34,760
On the other hand,

2607
01:42:34,760 --> 01:42:37,370
if you take the potential associated

2608
01:42:37,370 --> 01:42:39,980
with the core of the atom,

2609
01:42:40,820 --> 01:42:41,800
the nucleus,

2610
01:42:41,800 --> 01:42:44,420
that has a sharp feature in it,

2611
01:42:44,520 --> 01:42:47,560
and that sharp feature will,

2612
01:42:47,560 --> 01:42:49,700
if an electron wave comes and hits it,

2613
01:42:49,820 --> 01:42:51,440
will scatter it all over the place.

2614
01:42:52,300 --> 01:42:54,940
So it's an interplay between the

2615
01:42:54,940 --> 01:42:57,580
mass and the sharpness of the potential.

2616
01:42:58,280 --> 01:43:00,830
So can you do that experiment with a nucleus

2617
01:43:00,830 --> 01:43:03,380
and an electron and show that it actually does behave?

2618
01:43:03,380 --> 01:43:04,100
Absolutely.

2619
01:43:07,100 --> 01:43:07,580
Yup.

2620
01:43:12,900 --> 01:43:14,360
And isn't that what led to it?

2621
01:43:14,380 --> 01:43:16,980
Of course you can do it with an electron.

2622
01:43:16,980 --> 01:43:17,960
No problem with an electron.

2623
01:43:17,960 --> 01:43:18,520
Very easy.

2624
01:43:19,140 --> 01:43:21,880
The classic experiment was done in 1911.

2625
01:43:23,260 --> 01:43:25,220
It wasn't done with electrons.

2626
01:43:26,360 --> 01:43:28,140
It was done with alpha particles.

2627
01:43:30,860 --> 01:43:33,360
Alpha particles come in and hit a group of electrons.

2628
01:43:33,360 --> 01:43:33,880
And the result was a gold nucleus.

2629
01:43:34,240 --> 01:43:36,600
A gold nucleus is a small thing.

2630
01:43:37,300 --> 01:43:40,280
And the result was that the gold nucleus,

2631
01:43:40,500 --> 01:43:42,080
when the alpha particle comes in,

2632
01:43:42,120 --> 01:43:42,460
the wave,

2633
01:43:42,460 --> 01:43:45,700
the quantum mechanical wave of alpha particles comes in,

2634
01:43:46,360 --> 01:43:47,930
hits that tiny gold nucleus and

2635
01:43:47,930 --> 01:43:49,500
it gets scattered in all directions.

2636
01:43:51,160 --> 01:43:55,420
That's why Rutherford was a bit surprised to see

2637
01:43:55,420 --> 01:43:59,680
his alpha particles get scattered right back at him.

2638
01:44:00,400 --> 01:44:01,600
And what did it tell him?

2639
01:44:01,600 --> 01:44:04,080
It told him that the nucleus was very small.

2640
01:44:05,480 --> 01:44:05,920
Right.

2641
01:44:11,720 --> 01:44:13,580
But he didn't understand quantum mechanics.

2642
01:44:14,280 --> 01:44:14,420
No,

2643
01:44:14,420 --> 01:44:14,660
he didn't.

2644
01:44:14,660 --> 01:44:16,360
Right.

2645
01:44:20,820 --> 01:44:23,220
He just thought he had a beam of alpha particles,

2646
01:44:23,220 --> 01:44:24,980
some of which hit the center,

2647
01:44:24,980 --> 01:44:26,360
some of which went through here.

2648
01:44:27,500 --> 01:44:27,940
Right.

2649
01:44:27,940 --> 01:44:29,980
But in fact,

2650
01:44:29,980 --> 01:44:31,400
what he really had was a wave.

2651
01:44:33,400 --> 01:44:34,840
And the wave came in,

2652
01:44:34,840 --> 01:44:37,230
hit the tiny gold nucleus and

2653
01:44:37,230 --> 01:44:39,620
got scattered all over the place.

2654
01:44:42,940 --> 01:44:44,120
And with electrons,

2655
01:44:44,120 --> 01:44:44,820
yeah,

2656
01:44:44,820 --> 01:44:45,060
sure,

2657
01:44:45,060 --> 01:44:45,680
it's very easy.

2658
01:44:50,940 --> 01:44:53,520
That's what happens in accelerators

2659
01:44:53,520 --> 01:44:56,100
when electrons hit small targets.

2660
01:44:56,920 --> 01:44:58,180
They just get...

2661
01:44:58,180 --> 01:44:59,540
Photons do also.

2662
01:45:01,060 --> 01:45:02,140
Photons do also.

2663
01:45:02,820 --> 01:45:03,660
Electromagnetic waves,

2664
01:45:03,660 --> 01:45:04,420
if they hit,

2665
01:45:04,420 --> 01:45:06,780
you know,

2666
01:45:06,780 --> 01:45:10,600
structured objects with a structure smaller,

2667
01:45:10,600 --> 01:45:12,060
a size smaller than the wavelength,

2668
01:45:12,300 --> 01:45:13,600
they get scattered all over the place.

2669
01:45:18,980 --> 01:45:21,280
If they hit very smooth things,

2670
01:45:22,700 --> 01:45:26,080
they tend to propagate according to the geometric optics.

2671
01:45:26,080 --> 01:45:28,080
For example,

2672
01:45:28,080 --> 01:45:31,660
if you have a piece of

2673
01:45:31,660 --> 01:45:35,240
material with a position-varying index of refraction,

2674
01:45:36,080 --> 01:45:39,430
if that index of refraction is varying very smoothly

2675
01:45:39,430 --> 01:45:42,780
and very slowly over the wavelength of the photon,

2676
01:45:43,160 --> 01:45:46,220
then geometric optics is a good approximation.

2677
01:45:46,620 --> 01:45:47,280
If,

2678
01:45:47,280 --> 01:45:47,920
on the other hand,

2679
01:45:47,920 --> 01:45:51,990
you have a diffraction grating of

2680
01:45:51,990 --> 01:45:56,060
distance comparable or smaller to the wavelength,

2681
01:45:56,060 --> 01:45:58,660
the diffraction grating will spread

2682
01:45:58,660 --> 01:46:01,260
it out all over the place.

2683
01:46:02,460 --> 01:46:04,320
So it's not just electrons.

2684
01:46:04,320 --> 01:46:04,980
Electrons,

2685
01:46:04,980 --> 01:46:05,360
photons,

2686
01:46:05,360 --> 01:46:07,080
anything.

2687
01:46:10,760 --> 01:46:11,200
Okay.

2688
